        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 25 at 3:57PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 357 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Redbone, or near
Barnesville, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Barnesville, Forsyth, Yatesville, Aldora, Redbone, Blount, Goggins,
Berner, Collier, Johnstonville, and Brent.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
